<br>
-Switch to 3rd person view.  Makes targeting and situational awareness MUCH easier.  I use the last 3rd person view so that I can go back to 1st person w/ one button press.<br>
-Use mouselook (hold right mouse button and move mouse to move camera angle) to aid you in targeting and situational awareness.<br>
-Equip that wind instrument.  It helps.<br>
-Put on your CHA gear.  CHA should be around 125-140.  Actually I do alright with mine at about 115-120.  Point is, it makes a difference.<br>
-If you have more than 2 mobs mezzed and you get a resist, don't keep trying to mez that same mob.  If you move on to the others, you will only have one mob beating on you and you will sustain the MR debuff on the mezzed ones, making them easier to keep mezzed.  If you keep trying to mez the one that resisted, then all the others will wake up and you'll take a severe beating.<br>
-Bard mez songs have a push or pull effect depending on which song you're using.  Use this to your advantage to position mobs.  This will make targeting easier and can keep you from getting adds in some situations.<br>
-Learn to use your lull song in combination with Mez.  You can lull wandering mobs before they agro your group.<br>
-Know when you're beat, and let the group know what you can and can't mez.  <br>
<br>
To quote a 53+ bard who was mezzing 4 mobs while his group was med/healing up from a tough fight,  when asked by a group member, 'How long can you keep them mezzed like that?'<br>
The bard replied, 'Till we get a fifth.'<br>
<br>
Hope this helps<br>
-Auff <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxetan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xetan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grumpy Young Man</span><br>  Posts: 625<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/12/01 11:18:00 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/bardtr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Bard Questions</span><hr size=1> Forgive my ignorance, but is it safe to say that if I'm trying to do some crowd control I shouldn't be in the fight hacking and slashing?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uauffkee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Auff Kee</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/12/01 11:23:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/bardtr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Bard Questions</span><hr size=1> Absolutely.  If you are on crowd control, you have no business hitting anything.  If your in a group that needs you for CC and damage output, then you're in the wrong group.<br>
