</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 474<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/12/01 2:32:02 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae5.gif height=158 width=119></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/bardtr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Bard Questions</span><hr size=1> Well first let's examine the tools you have to work with at 33rd level:<br>
<br>
Kelin's Lucid Lullaby (AE Enthrall)<br>
Solon's Song of the Sirens (Targeted Charm)<br>
Crission's Pixie Strike (Targeted Mez)<br>
<br>
Ok first thing is to forget you even bought Lucid Lullaby. Verant made sure that song never will work.<br>
<br>
Now the other two songs you will varry in use depending on your partys composition.  If you have a good Cleric and perhaps a Paladin or some other class that can quickly generate some Hate to help you then Charm can be one of your most effective forms of CC. In pulls involving only one add I prefer to charm the add and shorten the fight.<br>
<br>
If there is not a Cleric present I usually prefer to mez extras.  Pixie Strike used to be next to useless but now is much improved.  I would say the limit of your CC ability with this song is 3 adds if you are very good. 2 adds if you are on a laggy connection or have lag due to your computer.<br>
<br>
One of the biggest benefits that Bards have is our ability to move while signing.  USe this to your benefit.  Use the &quot;push effect&quot; of Pixie to help position the MOB's where you want them.  Another major tip is that you only need to keep the MOB you want to mez targeted long enough to start the song.  After the song is started it is going to hit the targeted MOB no matter what you do short of stopping the song.  Use this to your atvantage by targeting the next MOB you need to mez.  This will save you valuable seconds.<br>
<br>
As far as melee'ing while you are CC......why not?  If you are good at twisting and targeting by all means hit that &quot;assist&quot; button and take some swings at the MOB being beat on by the party.  Just make sure to allow yourself ample time to re-apply charm or mez.  The ability to fight while performing CC duties and the ability to take more melee shots while doing it is what sets Bards above Enchanters for certain CC situations. <p><font size=2 face="Tempus Sans ITC, Verdana, Helvetica">
